LEGIONELLOSIS - PORTUGAL: (LISBON) NOSOCOMIAL, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
**********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 31 Jan 2018
Source: Xinhua News Agency [edited]
http://www.china.org.cn/world/Off_the_Wire/2018-02/01/content_50372135.htm


The number of people infected in the latest [legionellosis] outbreak in Portugal climbed to 13 on [Wed 21 Jan 2018], the country's Directorate-General of Health (DGS) announced. The outbreak was first reported on [Sun 28 Jan 2018], with 4 cases detected at the CUF Descobertas Hospital in Lisbon.

The number of infected has since risen to 13, of whom 9 are female and 3 are in intensive care.

The hospital's shower system is thought to be the most likely cause, with sink taps being investigated too.

_Legionella_ [are] bacteria that live in water. They are best known as the bacteria that cause legionnaire's disease, a serious form of pneumonia.

In 2017, 233 cases of [legionellosis] were detected in Portugal.

In 2014, a [legionellosis] outbreak in Vila Franca de Xira, a region in the east of Lisbon district, infected 375 and killed 12.

