[The source of this nosocomial outbreak of legionellosis is thought to be the hospital's potable water system, unlike last year's (2017) nosocomial outbreak at another Lisbon hospital, where the hospital's cooling system was thought to be the problem. Molecular typing clinical and environmental isolates of _Legionella_ can help delineate transmission pathways. More information on the outbreak would be appreciated from knowledgeable sources.

A map showing the location of CUF Descobertas Hospital in Lisbon can be found at https://goo.gl/maps/ae57KH6gYoC2. - Mod.ML

